            <div>
            <p>In the India, all 28 states and 8 union territories issue by the MEA india.<br>In 1961, many countries joined together to create a simplified method of &ldquo;legalizing&rdquo; documents for universal recognition.<br>Members of the conference, referred to as the Hague Convention, adopted a document referred to as an legalizationthat recognize by all member countries.<br>Since 23 November 2006 , the India has been part of the 1961 Hague Convention abolishing the Requirement of Legalization.<br>The legalization Convention provides the simplified certification of public (including notarized) documents to be used in countries that have joined the convention.<br>Documents destined for use in participating countries and their territories certifie by one of the officials in the jurisdiction in which the document execute.<br>The legalizationConvention requires that all Apostille&rsquo;s be numbered consecutively, with individual numbers applied to each legalization issue.<br>The recognized standard legalizationcontains a seal and below 9 to 17 mandatory references:<br>name of country from which the document emanates,<br>name of person signing the document,<br>the capacity in which the person signing the document act,<br>in the case of unsigned documents,<br>the name of the authority that has affixed the seal or stamp,<br>place of certification date of certification,<br>the authority issue the certificate,<br>certificate of number,<br>seal or stamp of authority of issue certificate and signature of authority issue certificate.</p>
