              array('id' => '12','category_id' => '1','name' => 'WHAT IS APOSTILLE ATTESTATION?','slug' => 'what-is-apostille-attestation','description' => '<ol>
            <li>In the India, all 28 states and 8 union territories issue by the MEA india.</li>
            <li>In 1961, many countries joined together to create a simplified method of &ldquo;legalizing&rdquo; documents for universal recognition.</li>
            <li>Members of the conference, referred to as the Hague Convention, adopted a document referred to as an Apostille that recognize by all member countries.</li>
            <li>Since&nbsp;<a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=which+date+india+is+part+of+hague&amp;oq=which+date+india+is+part+of+hague&amp;aqs=chrome..69i57j33.10778j0j8&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;ie=UTF-8">23 November 2006</a>&nbsp;, the India has been part of the 1961 Hague Convention abolishing the Requirement of Legalization.</li>
            <li>The Apostille Convention provides the simplified certification of public (including notarized) documents to be used in countries that have joined the convention.</li>
            <li>Documents destined for use in participating countries and their territories certifie by one of the officials in the jurisdiction in which the document execute.</li>
            <li>The Apostille Convention requires that all Apostille&rsquo;s be numbered consecutively, with individual numbers applied to each Apostille issue.</li>
            <li>The recognized standard Apostille contains a seal and below 9 to 17 mandatory references:</li>
            <li>name of country from which the document emanates,&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</li>
            <li>name of person signing the document,&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>
            <li>the capacity in which the person signing the document act,&nbsp;</li>
            <li>in the case of unsigned documents,&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>
            <li>the name of the authority that has affixed the seal or stamp,&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</li>
            <li>place of certification date of certification,&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</li>
            <li>the authority issue the certificate,</li>
            <li>certificate of number,&nbsp;</li>
            <li>seal or stamp of authority of issue certificate and signature of authority&nbsp; issue certificate.</li>
            </ol>
